div.font:
#...Sign into GCP
#...Open Google Cloud Shell
#...Create 2 sessions and run

gcloud compute zones list
gcloud config set compute/zone us-east1-b

wget https://storage.googleapis.com/golang/go1.6.2.linux-amd64.tar.gz
sudo rm -rf /usr/local/go
sudo tar -C /usr/local -xzf go1.6.2.linux-amd64.tar.gz
echo "export GOPATH=~/go" >> ~/.bashrc
source ~/.bashrc

mkdir -p $GOPATH/src/github.com/udacity
cd $GOPATH/src/github.com/udacity
git clone https://github.com/udacity/ud615
cd ud615/app

mkdir bin
cd monolith
go get -u
cd ..
go build -o ./bin/monolith .monolith
sudo ./bin/monolith -http :10080

TOKEN=$(curl http://127.0.0.1:10080/login -u user | jq -r '.token')
echo $TOKEN
curl -H "Authorization: Bearer $TOKEN" http://127.0.0.1:10080/secure

div.div:
- Download latest go package
- Delete current go dir
- Unzip new go package in /usr/local
- Set the go path to a new folder in home dir
- GOPATH must be set in order to get, build, and install packages. It should point to workspace, not go installation.

div.div:
Build Monolith App
- go get adds dependiencies to current module and installs them
- `go get` downloads and saves in $GOPATH/src/<import>, then executes go install, compared to go install which skips the part with downloading packages, and just compiles. After running go get, you should see bin and pkg added the GOPATH.
- build compiles but does not install
